snippet.textDisplay: This is literally the process that every person that does regular plait braids has to go through - we have to take out the braids (which takes hours, sometimes days - depending on the thickness and length) , then have wash day, then we have to put products to take care of our hair, then we get it rebraided (again, usually hours or days)... So this isn't that big of a deal to us. From the big pile of hair on the floor to the arm aches from holding them up for so long and going out of the house with half done hair, the process is so normal for us 😊😊😊  the reactions from other cultures is giving me so much laughs 😅😅😅

snippet.textDisplay: I have five years of free-form dreadlocks. I started with around 75 but have brushed out quite a few to have some loose hair with the dreads, I have around 50 now. The reason you lose so much hair is this: people with normal hair lose hair every day. When you have dreadlocks you don't really lose any hair bc it grows into (or gets sucked up into) the dreadlocks. That's how they get thicker over time. When I brushed out the 20 plus locks I had a huge bag of hair left over.
